cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.NE 

The paper deals with adversarial attacks against a system of monocular depth estimation based on convolutional neural networks, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The paper also proposes a defense method, which involves training another CNN to predict a saliency map, indicating the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the security of the MDE system, which falls under the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of neural networks, which falls under the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
